<inglise> COUNCIL DIRECTIVE 92/59/EEC of 29 June 1992 on general product safetey </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 92/59/EM&Uuml; &uuml;ldise tooteohutuse kohta 29. juuni 1992 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 100a thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 100a, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission(1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> In cooperation with the European Parliament(2), </inglise>
<eesti> koost&ouml;&ouml;s Euroopa Parlamendiga, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee(3) </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is important to adopt measures with the aim of progressively establishing the internal market over a period expiring on 31 December 1992; whereas the internal market is to comprise an area without internal frontiers in which the free movement of goods, persons, services and capital is ensured; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: siseturu j&auml;rkj&auml;rguliseks v&auml;ljakujundamiseks t&auml;htajaga 31. detsember 1992 tuleb vastu v&otilde;tta meetmed; siseturg h&otilde;lmab sisepiirideta territooriumi, kus on tagatud kaupade, isikute, teenuste ja kapitali vaba liikumine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas some Member States have adopted horizontal legislation on product safety, imposing, in particular, a general obligation on economic operators to market only safe products; whereas those legislations differ in the level of protection afforded to persons; whereas such disparities and the absence of horizontal legislation in other Member States are liable to create barriers to trade and distortions of competition within the internal market; </inglise>
<eesti> m&otilde;ned liikmesriigid on vastu v&otilde;tnud tooteohutust k&auml;sitlevaid horisontaal&otilde;igusakte, millega eelk&otilde;ige pannakse ettev&otilde;tjatele &uuml;ldine kohustus turustada ainult ohutuid tooteid; need &otilde;igusaktid erinevad isikute kaitstuse taseme osas; niisugused erinevused ja horisontaal&otilde;igusaktide puudumine teistes liikmesriikides v&otilde;ivad p&otilde;hjustada kaubandust&otilde;kkeid ja konkurentsi moonutamist siseturul; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is very difficult to adopt Community legislation for every product which exists or may be developed; whereas there is a need for a broadly-based, legislative framework of a horizontal nature to deal with those products, and also to cover lacunae in existing or forthcoming specific legislation, in particular with a view to ensuring a high level of protection of safety and health of persons, as required by Article 100 a (3) of the Treaty; </inglise>
<eesti> on v&auml;ga raske v&otilde;tta vastu &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusakte iga olemasoleva v&otilde;i loodava toote kohta; selliste toodete k&auml;sitlemiseks on vaja laiap&otilde;hjalist horisontaalset &otilde;igusraamistikku, mis t&auml;idaks ka l&uuml;ngad olemasolevates v&otilde;i tulevastes eri&otilde;igusaktides, eelk&otilde;ige eesm&auml;rgiga tagada inimeste ohutuse ja tervise kaitstuse k&otilde;rge tase vastavalt asutamislepingu artikli 100a l&otilde;ikele 3; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is therefore necessary to establish on a Community level a general safety requirement for any product placed on the market that is intended for consumers or likely to be used by consumers; whereas certain second-hand goods should nevertheless be excluded by their nature; </inglise>
<eesti> seep&auml;rast tuleks &uuml;henduse tasandil kehtestada &uuml;ldised ohutusn&otilde;uded iga sellise turuleviidud toote kohta, mis on m&otilde;eldud tarbijatele v&otilde;i mida tarbijad t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt kasutavad; teatavad kasutatud kaubad tuleks siiski nende olemuse t&otilde;ttu v&auml;lja j&auml;tta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas production equipment, capital goods and other products used exclusively in the context of a trade or business are not covered by this Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolev direktiiv ei h&otilde;lma tootmisvahendeid, kapitalikaupu ja muid tooteid, mida kasutatakse &uuml;ksnes kaubandus- v&otilde;i &auml;rikontekstis; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in the absence of more specific safety provisions, within the framework of Community regulations, covering the products concerned, the provisions of this Directive are to apply; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevat direktiivi kohaldatakse juhul, kui &uuml;henduse m&auml;&auml;rustes ei ole eris&auml;tteid asjaomaste toodete ohutuse kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas when there are specific rules of Cummunity law, of the total harmonization type, and in particular rules adopted on the basis of the new approach, which lay down obligations regarding product safety, further obligations should not be imposed on economic operators as regards the placing on the market of products covered by such rules; </inglise>
<eesti> kui &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusaktides on t&auml;ielikult &uuml;htlustatud erieeskirjad, eriti vastavalt uuele l&auml;henemisviisile vastuv&otilde;etud eeskirjad, millega n&auml;hakse ette tooteohutusega seotud kohustused, ei v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tjatele panna selliste eeskirjade kohaldamisalasse kuuluvate toodete turuleviimisega seotud lisakohustusi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, when the provisions of specific Community regulations cover only certain aspects of safety or categories of risks in respect of the product concerned, the obligations of economic operators in respect of such aspects are determined solely by those provisions; </inglise>
<eesti> kui &uuml;henduse erim&auml;&auml;rused h&otilde;lmavad ainult asjaomaste toodetega seotud teatavaid ohutusaspekte v&otilde;i riskiklasse, m&auml;&auml;ratakse ettev&otilde;tja kohustused selliste aspektide suhtes ainult k&otilde;nealuste m&auml;&auml;ruste p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is appropriate to supplement the duty to observe the general safety requirement by an obligation on economic operators to supply consumers with relevant information and adopt measures commensurate with the characteristics of the products, enabling them to be informed of the risks that these products might present; </inglise>
<eesti> on asjakohane t&auml;iendada &uuml;ldiste ohutusn&otilde;uete j&auml;lgimise kohustust ettev&otilde;tjate kohustusega anda tarbijatele asjakohast teavet ja v&otilde;tta meetmeid, mis on vastavuses toodete omadustega ja v&otilde;imaldavad tarbijatel saada teavet toodetega kaasneda v&otilde;ivate riskide kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in the absence of specific regulations, criteria should be defined whereby product safety can be assessed; </inglise>
<eesti> erim&auml;&auml;ruste puudumisel tuleks kehtestada kriteeriumid, mille alusel tooteohutust hinnata; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Member States must establish authorities responsible for monitoring product safety and with powers to take the appropriate measures; </inglise>
<eesti> liikmesriigid peavad moodustama tooteohutuse j&auml;relevalve eest vastutavad asutused, kellel on volitus v&otilde;tta asjakohaseid meetmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary in particular for the appropriate measures to include the power for Member States to organize, immediately and efficiently, the withdrawal of dangerous products already placed on the market; </inglise>
<eesti> on vaja, et asjakohaste meetmete hulka kuuluvad eelk&otilde;ige liikmesriikide volitused organiseerida viivitamata ja t&otilde;husalt juba turule viidud ohtlike toodete turult k&otilde;rvaldamine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary for the preservation of the unity of the market to inform the Commission of any measure restricting the placing on the market of a product or requiring its withdrawal from the market except for those relating to an event which is local in effect and in any case limited to the territory of the Member State concerned; whereas such measures can be taken only in compliance with the provisions of the Treaty, and in particular Articles 30 to 36; </inglise>
<eesti> turu &uuml;htsuse s&auml;ilitamiseks on vaja teatada komisjonile k&otilde;ikidest meetmetest, mis takistavad toote turuleviimist v&otilde;i n&otilde;uavad selle turult k&otilde;rvaldamist, v&auml;lja arvatud meetmed, mis on seotud kohaliku t&auml;htsusega juhtumiga ja mille m&otilde;ju piirdub igal juhul ainult asjaomase liikmesriigi territooriumiga; selliseid meetmeid saab v&otilde;tta ainult koosk&otilde;las asutamislepinguga, eriti selle artiklitega 30-36; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this Directive applies without prejudice to the notification procedures in Council Directive 83/189/EEC of 28 March 1983 laying down a procedure for the provision of information in the field of technical standards and regulations(4) and in Commission Decision 88/383/EEC of 24 February 1988 providing for the improvement of information on safety, hygiene and health at work(5); </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevat direktiivi kohaldatakse, ilma et see piiraks teatamise korda, mis on ette n&auml;htud n&otilde;ukogu 28. m&auml;rtsi 1983. aasta direktiiviga 83/189/EM&Uuml;, milles on s&auml;testatud standardite ja tehniliste normide kohta k&auml;iva teabe esitamise kord, (4) ja komisjoni 24. veebruari 1988. aasta otsusega 88/383/EM&Uuml;, millega n&auml;hakse ette t&ouml;&ouml;ohutust, -h&uuml;gieeni ja -tervishoidu k&auml;sitleva teabe t&otilde;hustamine; (5) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas effective supervision of product safety requires the setting-up at national and Community levels of a system of rapid exchange of information in emergency situations in respect of the safety of a product and whereas the procedure laid down by Council Decision 89/45/EEC of 21 December 1988 on a Community system for the rapid exchange of information on dangers arising from the use of consumer products(6) should therefore be incorporated into this Directive and the above Decision should be repealed; whereas it is also advisable for this Directive to take over the detailed procedures adopted under the above Decision and to give the Commission, assisted by a committee, power to adapt them; </inglise>
<eesti> tooteohutuse t&otilde;husaks j&auml;relevalveks tuleb siseriiklikul ja &uuml;henduse tasandil luua tooteohutust k&auml;sitlev kiire teabevahetuse s&uuml;steem erakorralisteks juhtudeks ja seep&auml;rast tuleks menetlus, mis on ette n&auml;htud n&otilde;ukogu 21. detsembri 1988. aasta otsusega 89/45/EM&Uuml; tarbekaupade kasutamisest tulenevaid ohte puudutava &uuml;henduse kiire teabevahetuse s&uuml;steemi kohta, (6) k&auml;esolevasse direktiivi inkorporeerida ja k&otilde;nealune otsus t&uuml;histada; samuti on soovitatav, et k&auml;esolev direktiiv v&otilde;taks &uuml;le eespool nimetatud otsusega vastuv&otilde;etud &uuml;ksikasjalikud menetlused ja annaks komisjonile volitused nende kohandamiseks komitee abil; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, moreover, equivalent notification procedures already exist for pharmaceuticals, which come under Directives 75/319/EEC(7) and 81/851/EEC(8), concerning animal diseases referred to in Directive 82/894/EEC(9), for products of animal origin covered by Directive 89/662/EEC(10), and in the form of the system for the rapid exchange of information in radiological emergencies under Decision 87/600/Euratom(11); </inglise>
<eesti> samav&auml;&auml;rne teatamise kord kehtib juba direktiivides 75/319/EM&Uuml; (7) ja 81/851/EM&Uuml; (8) k&auml;sitletavate farmaatsiatoodete, direktiivis 82/894/EM&Uuml; (9) k&auml;sitletavate loomahaiguste, direktiivis 89/662/EM&Uuml; (10) k&auml;sitletavate loomse p&auml;ritoluga toodete puhul ja otsusega 87/600/Euratom (11) etten&auml;htud kiire teabevahetuse s&uuml;steemi vormis kiirgusavarii korral; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is primarily for Member States, in compliance with the Treaty and in particular with Articles 30 to 36 thereof, to take appropriate measures with regard to dangerous products located within their territory; </inglise>
<eesti> on eelk&otilde;ige liikmesriikide kohus v&otilde;tta koosk&otilde;las asutamislepinguga, eriti selle artiklitega 30-36, asjakohaseid meetmeid nende territooriumidel paiknevate ohtlike toodete suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in such a situation the decision taken on a particular product could differ from one Member State to another; whereas such a difference may entail unacceptable disparities in consumer protection and constitute a barrier to intra-Community trade; </inglise>
<eesti> sellises olukorras v&otilde;ivad teatava toote suhtes tehtud otsused liikmesriigiti erineda; selline erinevus v&otilde;ib kaasa tuua vastuv&otilde;etamatuid erinevusi tarbijakaitses ja takistada &uuml;hendusesisest kaubandust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it may be necessary to cope with serious product-safety problems which affect or could affect, in the immediate future, all or a large part of the Community and which, in view of the nature of the safety problem posed by the product cannot be dealt with effectively in a manner commensurate with the urgency of the problem under the procedures laid down in the specific rules of Community law applicable to the products or category of products in question; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ib olla vajalik lahendada t&otilde;siseid tooteohutuse probleeme, mis m&otilde;jutavad v&otilde;i v&otilde;ivad l&auml;hitulevikus m&otilde;jutada kogu &uuml;hendust v&otilde;i suurt osa sellest ja mida ei ole selle tootega kaasneva ohutusprobleemi olemuse t&otilde;ttu v&otilde;imalik t&otilde;husalt k&auml;sitleda viisil, mis vastaks probleemi kiireloomulisusele k&otilde;nealuste toodete v&otilde;i tooteliikide suhtes kohaldatavate &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusaktide erieeskirjadega etten&auml;htud korra kohaselt; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is therefore necessary to provide for an adequate mechanism allowing, in the last resort, for the adoption of measures applicable throughout the Community, in the form of a decision addressed to the Member States, in order to cope with emergency situations as mentioned above; whereas such a decision is not of direct application to economic operators and must be incorporated into a national instrument; whereas measures adopted under such a procedure can be no more than interim measures that have to be taken by the Commission assisted by a committee of representatives of the Member States; whereas, for reasons of cooperation with the Member States, it is appropriate to provide for a regulatory committee according to procedure III (b) of Decision 87/373/EEC(12); </inglise>
<eesti> seep&auml;rast tuleb ette n&auml;ha asjakohane mehhanism, mis v&otilde;imaldab viimase abin&otilde;una v&otilde;tta liikmesriikidele adresseeritud otsuse vormis &uuml;henduse k&otilde;igis osades kohaldatavaid meetmeid eespool nimetatud erakorraliste juhtude lahendamiseks; selline otsus ei ole ettev&otilde;tjate suhtes otseselt kohaldatav ja see tuleb inkorporeerida siseriiklikusse &otilde;igusesse; sellise korra kohaselt vastuv&otilde;etud meetmed saavad olla &uuml;ksnes ajutised ja neid peab v&otilde;tma komisjon, keda abistab liikmesriikide esindajatest koosnev komitee; liikmesriikidevahelise koost&ouml;&ouml; huvides on asjakohane n&auml;ha ette otsuse 87/373/EM&Uuml; (12) III menetluse punktile b vastav regulatiivkomitee; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this Directive does not affect victims' rights within the meaning of Council Directive 85/374/EEC of 25 July 1985 on the approximation of the laws, regulations and administrative provisions of the Member States concerning liability for defective products(13) </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolev direktiiv ei m&otilde;juta n&otilde;ukogu 25. juuli 1985. aasta direktiivis 85/374/EM&Uuml; (liikmesriikide tootevastutust k&auml;sitlevate &otilde;igusnormide &uuml;htlustamise kohta) (13) nimetatud kahjukannataja &otilde;igusi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary that Member States provide for appropriate means of redress before the competent courts in respect of measures taken by the competent authorities which restrict the placing on the market of a product or require its withdrawal; </inglise>
<eesti> on oluline, et liikmesriigid n&auml;evad p&auml;devas kohtus ette asjakohased heastamisvahendid p&auml;devate asutuste v&otilde;etud meetmete suhtes, mis piiravad toote turuleviimist v&otilde;i n&otilde;uavad selle turult k&otilde;rvaldamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is appropriate to consider, in the light of experience, possible adaptation of this Directive, particularly as regards extension of its scope and provisions on emergency situations and intervention at Community level; </inglise>
<eesti> on asjakohane kaaluda omandatud kogemuste p&otilde;hjal k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohandamist, eelk&otilde;ige selle kohaldamisala laiendamise ning eriolukordi ja &uuml;henduse tasandil sekkumist k&auml;sitlevate s&auml;tete osas; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in addition, the adoption of measures concerning imported products with a view to preventing risks to the safety and health of persons must comply with the Community's international obligations, </inglise>
<eesti> v&auml;ltimaks riski inimeste ohutusele ja tervisele, peab importtooteid k&auml;sitlevate meetmete vastuv&otilde;tmine olema koosk&otilde;las &uuml;henduse rahvusvaheliste kohustusega, </eesti>
