<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The purpose of the provisions of this Directive is to ensure that products placed on the market are safe. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on tagada turuleviidud toodete ohutus. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions of this Directive shall apply in so far as there are no specific provisions in rules of Community law governing the safety of the products concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat direktiivi kohaldatakse niiv&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusaktides ei ole asjaomaste toodete ohutust reguleerivaid erieeskirju. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular, where specific rules of Community law contain provisions imposing safety requirements on the products which they govern, the provisions of Articles 2 to 4 of this Directive shall not, in any event, apply to those products. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusaktide erieeskirjades on s&auml;tted, mis kehtestavad ohutusn&otilde;uded neis eeskirjades h&otilde;lmatud toodetele, ei kohaldata nende toodete suhtes mingil juhul k&auml;esoleva direktiivi artikleid 2-4. </eesti>
<inglise> Where specific rules of Community law contain provisions governing only certain aspects of product safety or categories of risks for the products concerned, those are the provisions which shall apply to the products concerned with regard to the relevant safety aspects or risks. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusaktide erieeskirjades on s&auml;tted, mis reguleerivad ainult asjaomaste toodetega seotud tooteohutuse v&otilde;i riskiklasside teatavaid aspekte, kohaldatakse asjaomaste toodetega seotud ohutusaspektide v&otilde;i riskide suhtes neid s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) product shall mean any product intended for consumers or likely to be used by consumers, supplied whether for consideration or not in the course of a commercial activity and whether new, used or reconditioned. </inglise>
<eesti> a) toode - iga uus, kasutatud v&otilde;i uuendatud toode, mis on m&otilde;eldud tarbijatele v&otilde;i mida tarbijad t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt kasutavad ja mida tarnitakse kaubandusliku tegevuse raames tasu eest v&otilde;i tasuta. </eesti>
<inglise> However, this Directive shall not apply to second-hand products supplied as antiques or as products to be repaired or reconditioned prior to being used, provided that the supplier clearly informs the person to whom he supplies the product to that effect; </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat direktiivi ei kohaldata siiski kasutatud toodete suhtes, mida tarnitakse antiikesemetena, v&otilde;i enne nende kasutamist parandatavate v&otilde;i uuendatavate toodetena, tingimusel et tarnija teatab sellest selgelt isikule, kellele ta toodet tarnib; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) safe product shall mean any product which, under normal or reasonably foreseeable conditions of use, including duration, does not present any risk or only the minimum risks compatible with the product's use, considered as acceptable and consistent with a high level of protection for the safety and health of persons, taking into account the following points in particular: </inglise>
<eesti> b) ohutu toode - iga toode, mis tavalistes v&otilde;i eeldatavates kasutustingimustes, sealhulgas kasutusaeg, ei p&otilde;hjusta riske v&otilde;i p&otilde;hjustab toote kasutusele vastavalt minimaalset riski, ning mida loetakse aktsepteeritavaks ning inimeste ohutuse ja tervise kaitse k&otilde;rgele tasemele vastavaks, v&otilde;ttes eelk&otilde;ige arvesse j&auml;rgmisi punkte: </eesti>
<inglise> - the characteristics of the product, including its composition, packaging, instructions for assembly and maintenance, </inglise>
<eesti> - toote omadused, sealhulgas koostis, pakend ning kokkupanemis- ja hooldamisjuhendid, </eesti>
<inglise> - the effect on other products, where it is reasonably foreseeable that it will be used with other products, </inglise>
<eesti> - m&otilde;ju teistele toodetele, kui v&otilde;ib eeldada selle kasutamist koos teiste toodetega, </eesti>
<inglise> - the presentation of the product, the labelling, any instructions for its use and disposal and any other indication or information provided by the producer, </inglise>
<eesti> - toote esitusviis, m&auml;rgistus, toote kasutus- ja h&auml;vitamisjuhendid ning muud tootja m&auml;rkused v&otilde;i teated, </eesti>
<inglise> - the categories of consumers at serious risk when using the product, in particular children. </inglise>
<eesti> - tarbijagrupid, kes on toodet kasutades t&otilde;siselt ohustatud, eriti lapsed. </eesti>
<inglise> The feasibility of obtaining higher levels of safety or the availability of other products presenting a lesser degree of risk shall not constitute grounds for considering a product to be 'unsafe' or 'dangerous'; </inglise>
<eesti> V&otilde;imalus ohutust suurendada v&otilde;i muude v&auml;iksema riskiastmega toodete olemasolu ei ole piisav p&otilde;hjus pidada toodet "mitte ohutuks" v&otilde;i "ohtlikuks"; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) dangerous product shall mean any product which does not meet the defintion of 'safe product' according to point (b) hereof; </inglise>
<eesti> c) ohtlik toode - iga toode, mis ei vasta k&auml;esoleva artikli punktis b antud "ohutu toote" m&auml;&auml;ratlusele; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) producer shall mean: </inglise>
<eesti> d) tootja: </eesti>
<inglise> - the manufacturer of the product, when he is established in the Community, and any other person presenting himself as the manufacturer by affixing to the product his name, trade mark or other dinstinctive mark, or the person who reconditions the product, </inglise>
<eesti> - toote valmistaja, kui ta asub &uuml;henduses, ja mis tahes isik, kes esitleb ennast valmistajana ja on lisanud tootele oma nime, kaubam&auml;rgi v&otilde;i muu eraldusm&auml;rgiga, v&otilde;i isik, kes toodet uuendab, </eesti>
<inglise> - the manufacturer's representative, when the manufacturer is not established in the Community or, if there is no representative established in the Community, the importer of the product, </inglise>
<eesti> - valmistaja esindaja, kui valmistaja ei asu &uuml;henduses, v&otilde;i importija, kui valmistajal ei ole &uuml;henduses esindajat, </eesti>
<inglise> - other professionals in the supply chain, insofar as their activities may affect the safety properties of a product placed on the market. </inglise>
