<inglise> TITLE II </inglise>
<eesti> II JAOTIS </eesti>
<inglise> General safety requirement </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;ldised ohutusn&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Producers shall be obliged to place only safe products on the market. </inglise>
<eesti> Tootjad on kohustatud viima turule ainult ohutuid tooteid. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Within the limits of their respective activities, producers shall: </inglise>
<eesti> Oma tegevusala piires tootjad: </eesti>
<inglise> - provide consumers with the relevant information to enable them to assess the risks inherent in a product throughout the normal or reasonably foreseeable period of its use, where such risks are not immediately obvious without adequate warnings, and to take precautions against those risks. </inglise>
<eesti> - annavad tarbijatele asjakohast teavet, et v&otilde;imaldada neil hinnata tootega kaasnevaid riske toote tavalise v&otilde;i oletatava kasutusaja jooksul, kui sellised riskid ei ole kohe ilmselged ilma asjakohase hoiatuseta, ja v&otilde;tta nende riskide vastu ettevaatusabin&otilde;usid. </eesti>
<inglise> Provision of such warnings does not, however, exempt any person from compliance with the other requirements laid down in this Directive, </inglise>
<eesti> Sellised hoiatused ei vabasta kedagi kohustusest j&auml;rgida muid k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga etten&auml;htud n&otilde;udeid, </eesti>
<inglise> - adopt measures commensurate with the characteristics of the products which they supply, to enable them to be informed of risks which these products might present and to take appropriate action including, if necessary, withdrawing the product in question from the market to avoid these risks. </inglise>
<eesti> - v&otilde;tavad tarnitavate toodete omadustele vastavaid meetmeid, et olla kursis nende toodetega kaasneda v&otilde;ivate riskidega ja v&otilde;tta nende riskide v&auml;ltimiseks asjakohaseid abin&otilde;usid, sealhulgas vajaduse korral k&otilde;nealuste toodete turult k&otilde;rvaldamine. </eesti>
<inglise> The above measures shall for example include, whenever appropriate, marking of the products or product batches in such a way that they can be identified, sample testing of marketed products, investigating complaints made and keeping distributors informed of such monitoring. </inglise>
<eesti> Eespool nimetatud meetmete hulka kuuluvad n&auml;iteks vajaduse korral toodete v&otilde;i tootepartiide m&auml;rgistus sellisel viisil, et neid on v&otilde;imalik identifitseerida, turuleviidud toodete pisteline kontroll, esitatud kaebuste uurimine ja levitajatele sellistest j&auml;relevalvemeetmetest teatamine. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Distributors shall be required to act with due care in order to help to ensure compliance with the general safety requirement, in particular by not supplying products which they know or should have presumed, on the basis of the information in their possession and as professionals, do not comply with this requirement. </inglise>
<eesti> Levitajad peavad kandma hoolt selle eest, et tagada &uuml;ldiste ohutusn&otilde;uete t&auml;itmine, eelk&otilde;ige j&auml;ttes tarnimata tooted, mille kohta nad nende valduses oleva teabe p&otilde;hjal kutset&ouml;&ouml;listena teavad v&otilde;i oleksid pidanud oletama, et need ei vasta n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular, within the limits of their respective activities, they shall participate in monitoring the safety of products placed on the market, especially by passing on information on product risks and cooperating in the action taken to avoid these risks. </inglise>
<eesti> Oma tegevusala piires osalevad nad eelk&otilde;ige turuleviidud toodete ohutuse j&auml;lgimises, eelk&otilde;ige edastades teavet tooteriskide kohta ja tehes koost&ouml;&ouml;d selliste riskide v&auml;ltimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where there are no specific Community provisions governing the safety of the products in question, a product shall be deemed safe when it conforms to the specific rules of national law of the Member State in whose territory the product is in circulation, such rules being drawn up in conformity with the Treaty, and in particular Articles 30 and 36 thereof, and laying down the health and safety requirements which the product must satisfy in order to be marketed. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui asjaomaste toodete ohutust ei reguleerita &uuml;henduse eris&auml;tetega, loetakse toode ohutuks, kui see vastab selle liikmesriigi siseriikliku &otilde;iguse erieeskirjadele, kelle territooriumil toode ringluses on, tingimusel et k&otilde;nealused eeskirjad on koostatud koosk&otilde;las asutamislepinguga, eriti selle artiklitega 30-36, ja nendega on ette n&auml;htud tervisekaitse- ja ohutusn&otilde;uded, millele toode peab vastama, et seda saaks turustada. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> In the absence of specific rules as referred to in paragraph 1, the conformity of a product to the general safety requirement shall be assessed having regard to voluntary national standards giving effect to a European standard or, where they exist, to Community technical specifications or, failing these, to standards drawn up in the Member State in which the product is in circulation, or to the codes of good practice in respect of health and safety in the sector concerned or to the state of the art and technology and to the safety which consumers may reasonably expect. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud erieeskirjade puudumise korral hinnatakse toote vastavust &uuml;ldistele ohutusn&otilde;uetele, v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa standardiga koosk&otilde;las olevaid vabatahtlikke siseriiklikke standardeid v&otilde;i v&otilde;imalikke &uuml;henduse tehnilisi n&auml;itajaid v&otilde;i nende puudumise korral selles liikmesriigis kehtestatud standardeid, kus toode on ringluses, v&otilde;i asjaomases sektoris tervishoiu ja ohutuse suhtes rakendatavaid h&auml;id tavasid v&otilde;i tehnika ja tehnoloogia taset ja ohutuse taset, mida tarbijad v&otilde;ivad p&otilde;hjendatult oodata. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Conformity of a product with the provisions mentioned in paragraphs 1 or 2 shall not bar the competent authorities of the Member States from taking appropriate measures to impose restrictions on its being placed on the market or to require its withdrawal from the market where there is evidence that, despite such conformity, it is dangerous to the health and safety of consumers. </inglise>
<eesti> Toote vastavus l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 nimetatud s&auml;tetele ei takista liikmesriikide p&auml;devatel asutustel v&otilde;tta asjakohaseid meetmeid, et kehtestada piiranguid toote turuleviimisele v&otilde;i n&otilde;uda selle turult k&otilde;rvaldamist, kui toode, hoolimata selle n&otilde;uetekohasusest, ohustab tarbijate tervist ja ohutust. </eesti>
<inglise> TITLE III </inglise>
<eesti> III JAOTIS </eesti>
<inglise> Obligations and powers of the Member States </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriikide kohustused ja volitused </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall adopt the necessary laws, regulations and administrative provisions to make producers and distributors comply with their obligations under this Directive in such a way that products placed on the market are safe. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad vastu vajalikud &otilde;igusnormid, millega tagada, et tootjad ja levitajad t&auml;idaksid k&auml;esolevas direktiivis s&auml;testatud kohustusi sellisel viisil, et turuleviidud tooted oleksid ohutud. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular, Member States shall establish or nominate authorities to monitor the compliance of products with the obligation to place only safe products on the market and arrange for such authorities to have the necessary powers to take the appropriate measures incumbent upon them under this Directive, including the possibility of imposing suitable penalties in the event of failure to comply with the obligations deriving from this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Eelk&otilde;ige moodustavad v&otilde;i nimetavad liikmesriigid asutused, kes j&auml;lgivad, et tooted vastavad ohutute toodete turuleviimise n&otilde;uetele, ja annavad sellistele asutustele vajalikud volitused, et v&otilde;tta neile k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga etten&auml;htud asjakohaseid meetmeid, sealhulgas v&otilde;imalus m&auml;&auml;rata asjakohaseid sanktsioone, kui k&auml;esolevast direktiivist l&auml;htuvaid kohustusi ei t&auml;ideta. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall notify the Commission of the said authorities; the Commission shall pass on the information to the other Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Nad teatavad nimetatud asutused komisjonile; komisjon edastab selle teabe teistele liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of Article 5, Member States shall have the necessary powers, acting in accordance with the degree or risk and in conformity with the Treaty, and in particular Articles 30 and 36 thereof, to adopt appropriate measures with a view, inter alia, to: </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 5 kohaldamisel on liikmesriikidel vajalikud volitused v&otilde;tta vastavalt riskiastmele ja koosk&otilde;las asutamislepinguga, eriti selle artiklitega 30 ja 36, asjakohaseid meetmeid, muu hulgas, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) organizing appropriate checks on the safety properties of products, even after their being placed on the market as being safe, on an adequate scale, up to the final stage of use or consumption; </inglise>
<eesti> a) organiseerida asjakohast toodete ohutusomaduste kontrolli ka p&auml;rast toodete ohutuna turuleviimist kuni nende viimase kasutus- v&otilde;i tarbimisetapini; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) requiring all necessary information from the parties concerned; </inglise>
<eesti> b) n&otilde;uda asjassepuutuvatelt isikutelt kogu vajalikku teavet; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) taking samples of a product or a product line and subjecting them to safety checks; </inglise>
<eesti> c) v&otilde;tta tootelt v&otilde;i tootesarjalt proove ja kontrollida nende ohutust; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) subjecting product marketing to prior conditions designed to ensure product safety and requiring that suitable warnings be affixed regarding the risks which the product may present; </inglise>
<eesti> d) esitada toote ohutuse tagamiseks selle turuleviimisele eeltingimused ja n&otilde;uda, et toode oleks varustatud asjakohaste hoiatustega sellega kaasneda v&otilde;ivate riskide kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) making arrangements to ensure that persons who might be exposed to a risk from a product are informed in good time and in a suitable manner of the said risk by, inter alia, the publication of special warnings; </inglise>
<eesti> e) teha korraldusi, millega tagada, et isikutele, kelle toode v&otilde;ib osutuda ohtlikuks, teatatakse v&otilde;imalikust ohust &otilde;igeaegselt ja asjakohaselt, avaldades muu hulgas erihoiatuse; </eesti>
<inglise> (f) temporarily prohibiting, for the period required to carry out the various checks, anyone from supplying, offering to supply or exhibiting a product or product batch, whenever there are precise and consistent indications that they are dangerous; </inglise>
<eesti> f) keelata ajutiselt kontrolli tegemiseks vajalikuks ajaks kellelgi toodet v&otilde;i tootepartiid tarnida, selle tarnimiseks ettepanekut teha v&otilde;i seda eksponeerida, kui selle ohtlikkuse kohta on t&auml;pseid ja j&auml;rjepidevaid t&otilde;endeid; </eesti>
<inglise> (g) prohibiting the placing on the market of a product or product batch which has proved dangerous and establishing the accompanying measures needed to ensure that the ban is complied with; </inglise>
<eesti> g) keelata ohtlikuks osutunud toote v&otilde;i tootepartii turule viimine ja v&otilde;tta sellega seoses keelu j&auml;rgimiseks vajalikud meetmed; </eesti>
<inglise> (h) organizing the effective and immediate withdrawal of a dangerous product or product batch already on the market and, if necessary, its destruction under appropriate conditions. </inglise>
<eesti> h) organiseerida juba turule viidud ohtliku toote v&otilde;i tootepartii t&otilde;hus ja viivitamatu turult k&otilde;rvaldamine ja vajaduse korral selle h&auml;vitamine asjakohastel tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The measures to be taken by the competent authorities of the Member States under this Article shall be addressed, as appropriate, to: </inglise>
<eesti> Meetmed, mida liikmesriikide p&auml;devad asutused k&auml;esoleva artikli kohaselt peavad v&otilde;tma, adresseeritakse vastavalt vajadusele j&auml;rgmistele isikutele: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the producer; </inglise>
<eesti> a) tootja; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) within the limits of their respective activities, distributors and in particular the party responsible for the first stage of distribution on the national market; </inglise>
<eesti> b) levitajad nende tegevusala piires ja eelk&otilde;ige isikud, kes vastutavad turustuse esimese etapi eest riigi siseturul; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) any other person, where necessary, with regard to cooperation in action taken to avoid risks arising from a product. </inglise>
<eesti> c) teised isikud, kui see osutub vajalikuks tootega kaasnevate riskide v&auml;ltimiseks tehtava koost&ouml;&ouml; seisukohast. </eesti>
<inglise> TITLE IV </inglise>
<eesti> IV JAOTIS </eesti>
<inglise> Notification and Exchanges of Information </inglise>
<eesti> Teavitamine ja teabevahetus </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a Member State takes measures which restrict the placing of a product or a product batch on the market or require its withdrawal from the market, such as provided for in Article 6 (1) (d) to (h), the Member State shall, to the extent that such notification is not required under any specific Community legislation, inform the Commission of the said measures, specifying its reasons for adopting them. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriik v&otilde;tab meetmeid, mis piiravad toote v&otilde;i tootepartii turuleviimist, v&otilde;i n&otilde;uab selle turult k&otilde;rvaldamist artikli 6 l&otilde;ike 1 punktide d-h kohaselt, teatab liikmesriik, kui selline teatamine ei ole ette n&auml;htud m&otilde;ne &uuml;henduse eri&otilde;igusaktiga, nimetatud meetmetest komisjonile ja t&auml;psustab nende v&otilde;tmise p&otilde;hjused. </eesti>
<inglise> This obligation shall not apply where the measures relate to an event which is local in effect and in any case limited to the territory of the Member State concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda kohustust ei kohaldata, kui meetmed on seotud kohaliku t&auml;htsusega juhtumiga ja nende m&otilde;ju piirdub igal juhul ainult asjaomase liikmesriigi territooriumiga. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall enter into consultations with the parties concerned as quickly as possible. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon peab asjaomaste osapooltega v&otilde;imalikult kiiresti n&otilde;u. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the Commission concludes, after such consultations, that the measure is justified, it shall immediately inform the Member State which initiated the action and the other Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui komisjon leiab p&auml;rast k&otilde;nealust n&otilde;upidamist, et meede on p&otilde;hjendatud, teatab ta sellest viivitamata meetme algatanud liikmesriigile ja teistele liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the Commission concludes, after such consultations, that the measures is not justified, it shall immediately inform the Member State which initiated the action. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui komisjon leiab p&auml;rast k&otilde;nealust n&otilde;upidamist, et meede ei ole p&otilde;hjendatud, teatab ta sellest viivitamata meetme algatanud liikmesriigile. </eesti>
<inglise> TITLE V </inglise>
<eesti> V JAOTIS </eesti>
<inglise> Emergency situations and action at Community level </inglise>
<eesti> Eriolukorrad ja meetmed &uuml;henduse tasandil </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a Member State adopts or decides to adopt emergency measures to prevent, restrict or impose specific conditions on the possible marketing or use, within its own territory, of a product or product batch by reason of a serious and immediate risk presented by the said product or product batch to the health and safety of consumers, it shall forthwith inform the Commission thereof, unless provision is made for this obligation in procedures of a similar nature in the context of other Community instruments. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriik v&otilde;tab v&otilde;i otsustab v&otilde;tta erakorralisi meetmeid, et toote v&otilde;i tootepartii v&otilde;imalikku turuleviimist v&otilde;i kasutamist oma territooriumil v&auml;ltida, piirata v&otilde;i sellele eritingimusi seada p&otilde;hjusel, et k&otilde;nealune toode v&otilde;i tootepartii kujutab t&otilde;sist ja otsest riski tarbijate tervisele ja ohutusele, teatab ta sellest viivitamata komisjonile, kui see kohustus ei ole ette n&auml;htud samalaadse menetlusega m&otilde;ne muu &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusakti raames. </eesti>
<inglise> This obligation shall not apply if the effects of the risk do not, or cannot, go beyond the territory of the Member State concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda kohustust ei kohaldata, kui riski m&otilde;ju ei ulatu v&otilde;i ei saa ulatuda asjaomase liikmesriigi territooriumist kaugemale. </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to the provisions of the first subparagraph, Member States may pass on to the Commission any information in their possession regarding the existence of a serious and immediate risk before deciding to adopt the measures in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks esimese l&otilde;igu kohaldamist, v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid edastada komisjonile mis tahes nende valduses oleva teabe t&otilde;sise ja otsese riski kohta enne, kui nad k&otilde;nealuseid meetmeid v&otilde;tta otsustavad. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> On receiving this information, the Commission shall check to see whether it complies with the provisions of this Directive and shall forward it to the other Member States, which, in turn, shall immediately inform the Commission of any measures adopted. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui komisjon on sellise teabe saanud, kontrollib ta teabe vastavust k&auml;esolevale direktiivile ja edastab selle teistele liikmesriikidele, kes omakorda teatavad viivitamata komisjonile k&otilde;ikidest v&otilde;etud meetmetest. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Detailed procedures for the Community information system described in this Article are set out in the Annex. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas artiklis kirjeldatud &uuml;henduse teabevahetuse s&uuml;steemi &uuml;ksikasjalik kord n&auml;hakse ette lisas. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall be adapted by the Commission in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 11. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon kohandab seda artiklis 11 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> If the Commission becomes aware, through notification given by the Member States or through information provided by them, in particular under Article 7 or Article 8, of the existence of a serious and immediate risk from a product to the health and safety of consumers in various Member States and if: </inglise>
<eesti> Kui komisjon teeb liikmesriikide esitatud teatise v&otilde;i teabe p&otilde;hjal ja eelk&otilde;ige artiklites 7 ja 8 nimetatud juhtudel kindlaks, et mingi toode kujutab eri liikmesriikides t&otilde;sist ja otsest ohtu tarbijate tervisele ja ohutusele, ja kui: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) one or more Member States have adopted measures entailing restrictions on the marketing of the product or requiring its withdrawal from the market, such as those provided for in Article 6 (1) (d) to (h); </inglise>
<eesti> a) &uuml;ks v&otilde;i mitu liikmesriiki on v&otilde;tnud artikli 6 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides d-h nimetatud meetmeid, millega piiratakse toote turuleviimist v&otilde;i n&otilde;utakse selle turult k&otilde;rvaldamist; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) Member States differ on the adoption of measures to deal with the risk in question; </inglise>
<eesti> b) k&otilde;nealuse riskiga seotud meetmete v&otilde;tmine erineb liikmesriigiti; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) the risk cannot be dealt with, in view of the nature of the safety issue posed by the product and in a manner compatible with the urgency of the case, under the other procedures laid down by the specific Community legislation applicable to the product or category of products concerned; and </inglise>
<eesti> c) riski ei saa v&auml;ltida tootega seotud ohutusk&uuml;simuse iseloomu t&otilde;ttu ja asja kiireloomulisusele vastaval viisil muude asjaomase toote v&otilde;i tooteliigi suhtes &uuml;henduse eri&otilde;igusaktidega etten&auml;htud menetluste kohaselt; ning </eesti>
<inglise> (d) the risk can be eliminated effectively only by adopting appropriate measures applicable at Community level, in order to ensure the protection of the health and safety of consumers and the proper functioning of the common market, </inglise>
<eesti> d) riski saab t&otilde;husalt k&otilde;rvaldada ainult v&otilde;ttes &uuml;henduse tasandil kohaldatavaid asjakohaseid meetmeid, et tagada tarbijate tervise ja ohutuse kaitse ning &uuml;histuru n&otilde;uetekohane toimimine, </eesti>
<inglise> the Commission, after consulting the Member States and at the request of at least one of them, may adopt a decision, in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 11, requiring Member States to take temporary measures from among those listed in Article 6 (1) (d) to (h). </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ib komisjon p&auml;rast liikmesriikidega konsulteerimist ja v&auml;hemalt &uuml;he liikmesriigi taotluse korral teha otsuse artiklis 11 s&auml;testatud korras, n&otilde;udes, et liikmesriigid v&otilde;taksid artikli 6 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides d-h loetletud ajutisi meetmeid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 10 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 10 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall be assisted by a Committee on Product Safety Emergencies, hereinafter referred to as 'the Committee', composed of the representatives of the Member States and chaired by a representative of the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni abistab tooteohutuse eriolukordade komitee, edaspidi "komitee", mis koosneb liikmesriikide esindajatest ja mida juhatab komisjoni esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to Article 9 (c), there shall be close cooperation between the Committee referred to in paragraph 1 and the other Committees established by specific rules of Community law to assist the Commission as regards the health and safety aspects of the product concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks artikli 9 punkti c kohaldamist, teevad l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud komitee ja teiste &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse erieeskirjadega moodustatud komiteed tihedat koost&ouml;&ouml;d, et abistada komisjoni asjaomase toote tervisekaitse ja ohutusega seotud aspektides. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 11 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 11 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission representative shall submit to the Committee a draft of the measures to be taken. </inglise>
<eesti> V&otilde;etavate meetmete eeln&otilde;u esitab komiteele komisjoni esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise> The Committee, having verified that the conditions listed in Article 9 are fulfilled, shall deliver its opinion on the draft within a time limit which the Chairman may lay down according to the urgency of the matter but which may not exceed one month. </inglise>
<eesti> Komitee esitab p&auml;rast artiklis 9 loetletud tingimuste t&auml;itmise kontrollimist eeln&otilde;u kohta oma arvamuse t&auml;htaja jooksul, mille m&auml;&auml;rab eesistuja l&auml;htuvalt k&uuml;simuse kiireloomulisusest, kuid mis ei ole pikem kui &uuml;ks kuu. </eesti>
<inglise> The opinion shall be delivered by the majority laid down in Article 148 (2) of the Treaty for adoption of decisions by the Council on a proposal from the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> Arvamus esitatakse sellise h&auml;&auml;lteenamusega, nagu on s&auml;testatud asutamislepingu artikli 148 l&otilde;ikes 2 n&otilde;ukogu otsuste vastuv&otilde;tmiseks komisjoni ettepaneku p&otilde;hjal. </eesti>
<inglise> The votes of the representatives of the Member States within the Committee shall be weighted in the manner set out in that Article. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriikide esindajate h&auml;&auml;li komitees arvestatakse nimetatud artiklis s&auml;testatud viisil. </eesti>
<inglise> The Chairman shall not vote. </inglise>
<eesti> Eesistuja ei h&auml;&auml;leta. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall adopt the measures in question, if they are in accordance with the opinion of the Committee. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui k&otilde;nealused meetmed on komitee arvamusega koosk&otilde;las, v&otilde;tab komisjon need vastu. </eesti>
<inglise> If the measures proposed are not in accordance with the Committee's opinion, or in the absence of an opinion, the Commission shall forthwith submit to the Council a proposal regarding the measures to be taken. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui ettepandud meetmed ei ole komitee arvamusega koosk&otilde;las v&otilde;i kui komitee ei esita oma arvamust, esitab komisjon v&otilde;etavate meetmete kohta viivitamata ettepaneku n&otilde;ukogule. </eesti>
<inglise> The Council shall act by a qualified majority. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu teeb otsuse kvalifitseeritud h&auml;&auml;lteenamusega. </eesti>
<inglise> If the Council has not acted whtih 15 days of the date on which the proposal was submitted to it, the measures proposed shall be adopted by the Commission unless the Council has decided against them by a simple majority. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui n&otilde;ukogu ei ole 15 p&auml;eva jooksul alates ettepaneku esitamise kuup&auml;evast otsust teinud, v&otilde;tab komisjon ettepandud meetmed vastu, kui n&otilde;ukogu ei ole lihth&auml;&auml;lteenamusega sellele vastu h&auml;&auml;letanud. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Any measure adopted under this procedure shall be valid for no longer than tree months. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;ik k&auml;esoleva korra alusel vastuv&otilde;etud meetmed kehtivad k&otilde;ige rohkem kolm kuud. </eesti>
<inglise> That period may be prolonged under the dame procedure. </inglise>
<eesti> Kehtivusaega v&otilde;ib pikendada sama menetluse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall take all necessary measures to implement the decisions adopted under this procedures within less than 10 days. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed, et rakendada k&auml;esoleva korra alusel tehtud otsuseid 10 p&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authorities of the Member States responsible for carrying out measures adopted under this procedures shall, within one month, give the parties concerned an opportunity to submit their views and shall inform the Commission accordingly. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva korra alusel v&otilde;etud meetmete rakendamise eest vastutavad liikmesriikide p&auml;devad asutused annavad &uuml;he kuu jooksul asjaomastele isikutele v&otilde;imaluse esitada oma seisukohad ja teatavad sellest komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 12 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 12 </eesti>
<inglise> The Member States and the Commission shall take the steps necessary to ensure that their officials and agents are required not to disclose information obtained for the purposes of this Directive which, by its nature, is covered by professional secrecy, except for information relating to the safety propertiies of a given product which must be made public if circumstances so require, in order to protect the health and safety of persons. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid ja komisjon v&otilde;tavad vajalikke meetmeid, millega tagada, et nende ametiisikud ja teenistujad ei avaldaks k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamiseks saadud teavet, mis kuulub ametisaladuse hoidmise kohustuse alla, v&auml;lja arvatud teatava toote ohutusomadustega seotud teave, mis tuleb inimeste tervise ja ohutuse kaitseks avalikustada, kui asjaolud seda n&otilde;uavad. </eesti>
<inglise> TITLE VI </inglise>
<eesti> VI JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> Miscellaneous and final provisions </inglise>
<eesti> Muud s&auml;tted ja l&otilde;pps&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise> Article 13 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 13 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive shall be without prejudice to Directive 85/374/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamine ei piira direktiivi 85/374/EM&Uuml; kohaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 14 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 14 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Any decision adopted under this Directive and involving restrictions on the placing of a product on the market, or requiring its withdrawal from the market, must state the appropriate reasons on which it is based. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;iki k&auml;esoleva direktiivi alusel tehtud otsuseid, mis k&auml;sitlevad toote turuleviimise piiramist v&otilde;i n&otilde;uavad selle turult k&otilde;rvaldamist, tuleb asjakohaselt p&otilde;hjendada. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall be notified as soon as possible to the party concerned and shall indicate the remedies available under the provisions in force in the Member State in question and the time limits applying to such remedies. </inglise>
<eesti> Otsused teatatakse asjaomastele isikutele niipea kui v&otilde;imalik ja neis m&auml;rgitakse &auml;ra k&otilde;nealuses liikmesriigis kehtivatel &otilde;igusaktidel p&otilde;hinevad heastamisvahendid ja selliste heastamisvahendite kohaldamise t&auml;htajad. </eesti>
<inglise> The parties concerned shall, whenever feasible, be given an opportunity to submit their views before the adoption of the measure. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui see on v&otilde;imalik, antakse enne meetme vastuv&otilde;tmist asjaomastele isikutele v&otilde;imalus esitada oma seisukohad. </eesti>
<inglise> If this has not been done in advance because of the urgency of the measures to be taken, such opportunity shall be given in due course after the measure has been implemented. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui seda pole v&otilde;etavate meetmete kiireloomulisuse t&otilde;ttu eelnevalt tehtud, antakse selline v&otilde;imalus sobival juhul p&auml;rast meetme rakendamist. </eesti>
<inglise> Measures requiring the withdrawal of a product from the market shall take into consideration the need to encourage distributors, users and consumers to contribute to the implementation of such measures. </inglise>
<eesti> Selliste meetmete puhul, mis n&otilde;uavad toote turult k&otilde;rvaldamist, v&otilde;etakse arvesse vajadust julgustada levitajaid, kasutajaid ja tarbijaid aitama kaasa nende meetmete rakendamisele. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that any measure taken by the competent authorities involving restrictions on the placing of a product on the market or requiring its withdrawal from the market can be challenged before the competent courts. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tagavad, et p&auml;devate asutuste v&otilde;etud meetmeid, mis k&auml;sitlevad toote turuleviimise piiramist v&otilde;i n&otilde;uavad selle turult k&otilde;rvaldamist, saab p&auml;devas kohtus vaidlustada. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Any decision taken by virtue of this Directive and involving restrictions on the placing of a product on the market or requiring its withdrawal from the market shall be entirely without prejudice to assessment of the liability of the party concernd, in the light of the national criminal law applying in the case in question. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaselt tehtud otsused, mis k&auml;sitlevad toote turuleviimise piiramist v&otilde;i n&otilde;uavad selle turult k&otilde;rvaldamist, ei piira mingil viisil asjaomaste isikute vastutuse hindamist k&otilde;nealuse juhtumi kohta kehtiva siseriikliku kriminaal&otilde;iguse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 15 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 15 </eesti>
<inglise> Every two years following the date of adoption, the Commission shall submit a report on the implementation of this Directive to the European Parliament and the Council. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon esitab Euroopa Parlamendile ja n&otilde;ukogule k&auml;esoleva direktiivi rakendamist k&auml;sitleva aruande iga kahe aasta j&auml;rel p&auml;rast selle vastuv&otilde;tmist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 16 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 16 </eesti>
<inglise> Four years from the date referred to in Article 17 (1), on the basis of a Commission report on the experience acquired, together with appropriate proposals, the Council shall decide whether to adjust this Directive, in particular with a view to extending its scope as laid down in Article 1 (1) and Article 2 (a), and whether the provisions of Title V should be amended. </inglise>
<eesti> Neli aastat p&auml;rast artikli 17 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud kuup&auml;eva otsustab n&otilde;ukogu saadud kogemustel p&otilde;hineva komisjoni aruande ja asjakohaste ettepanekute p&otilde;hjal, kas k&auml;esolevat direktiivi tuleb kohandada, eel&otilde;ige selleks, et laiendada selle artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 1 ja artikli 2 punktis a s&auml;testatud reguleerimisala, ja kas V jaotist tuleb muuta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 17 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 17 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall adopt the laws, regulations and administrative provisions necessary to comply with this Directive by 29 June 1994 at the latest. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&auml;rgimiseks vajalikud &otilde;igusnormid vastu hiljemalt 29. juuniks 1994. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall forthwith inform the Commission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Nad teatavad sellest viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions adopted shall apply with effect from 29 June 1994. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastuv&otilde;etud norme kohaldatakse alates 29. juunist 1994. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> When these measures are adopted by the Member States, they shall contain a reference to this Directive or be accompanied by such a reference on the occasion of their official publication. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriigid need normid vastu v&otilde;tavad, lisavad nad nendesse normidesse v&otilde;i nende normide ametliku avaldamise korral nende juurde viite k&auml;esolevale direktiivile. </eesti>
<inglise> The methods of making such a referenc shall be laid down by the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Viitamise viisi n&auml;evad ette liikmesriigid. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall communicate to the Commission the text of the provisions of national law which they adopt in the area covered by this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid edastavad komisjonile k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga reguleeritavas valdkonnas vastuv&otilde;etavate siseriiklike &otilde;igusnormide teksti. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 18 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 18 </eesti>
<inglise> Decision 89/45/EEC is hereby repealed on the date referred to in Article 17 (1). </inglise>
<eesti> Otsus 89/45/EM&Uuml; tunnistatakse kehtetuks artikli 17 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud kuup&auml;eval. </eesti>
